I think many champions need GAMEPLAY Updates, but I think less desperately need VGUs. The only ones I can think of currently that are very much outliers of the pack are:
{{champion:32}} {{champion:36}} {{champion:54}} {{champion:56}} {{champion:35}} {{champion:102}} {{champion:77}} 
These IMO are the only champions that need a Visual Update AND a Gameplay Update in the current state of the game. There are others that are close, but moreso need better gameplay than visuals, such as:
{{champion:12}} {{champion:7}} {{champion:90}} {{champion:72}} {{champion:17}} 
There is a few others that could use visual updates too with minor changes to gameplay, such as:
{{champion:34}} {{champion:53}} {{champion:79}} {{champion:24}} {{champion:117}} {{champion:33}} {{champion:26}} 
Thats about the list to me. I think about 3-4 VGUs a year would be about right, especially since the NEED between the champions on these lists vary a lot. For example, Shaco needs an update far, far more than Nocturne. And Skarner needs new gameplay much more than Alistar. And Jax needs a visual update far more than Rammus.
